<subSubSection id="E0C0657EE076FF93029BF88850019AFF" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A86536F5E076FF93029BF88853159E6A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1692,2043]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF92029BF888504A9809" bold="true" box="[199,335,1800,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">Discussion:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="77618857E076FF9203D7F88850E89809" box="[395,493,1800,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male and encrusted with what appear to be mineral deposits (
<figureCitation id="30E12A70E076FF9206B4F888542E9809" box="[1256,1323,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1036,1060]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetId="figure-85@3.[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Cryphocricos barozzii (1) holotype, (2) brachypterous female from Rosario River, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, (3) abdominal terga showing dark tubercles near middle of III–V, (4) subgenital plate of two specimens from Nova Teutonia, Brazil showing intrapopulational variation in shape of posterior margin. Figure 1 courtesy of NHMW Hemiptera Image Collection / Harald Bruckner and Herbert Zettel." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693075/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E076FF920719F8895067986D" author="Parsons, M. C. &amp; Hewson, R. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="74" pagination="510 - 527" refId="ref13384" refString="Parsons, M. C. &amp; Hewson, R. J. (1974) Plastral respiratory devices in adult Cryphocricos (Naucoridae: Heteroptera). Psyche, 81, 510 - 527. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 1974 / 30691" type="journal article" year="1974">Parsons &amp; Hewson (1974)</bibRefCitation>
used 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF9203F9F8AC531A986D" authorityName=": Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[421,543,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryptocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF9203F9F8AC531A986D" box="[421,543,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF92000AF8AC53F9986D" authorityName="Usinger" authorityYear="1947" box="[598,764,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungerfordi">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF92000AF8AC53F9986D" box="[598,764,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">C. hungerfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to study the morphology of the cuticle showing its plastron retention capability. Further, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E076FF920383F8D1538D9840" author="Parsons, M. C." box="[479,648,1872,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" pagination="119 - 151" refId="ref13432" refString="Parsons, M. C. (1966) Studies on the cephalic anatomy of Naucoridae (Heteroptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 118 (5), 119 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1966. tb 00836. x" type="journal article" year="1966">Parsons (1966)</bibRefCitation>
provided a comparative analysis of the cephalic anatomy among five genera of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF920356F8F4508E98A5" baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[266,395,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Naucoridae</taxonomicName>
and one of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF92004FF8F453D598A5" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1851" box="[531,720,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aphelocheiridae</taxonomicName>
. Later, Parsons (1974) studied the morphology of the pterothoracic intersegmental region including that of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF9200D4F81852049899" authorityName=": Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[648,769,1944,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryptocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF9200D4F81852049899" box="[648,769,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E076FF920152F81955149899" author="Lopez Ruf, M. L. &amp; Pellerano, G. N. &amp; Bachmann, A. O." box="[782,1041,1944,1971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" pagination="267 - 273" refId="ref13183" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L., Pellerano, G. N. &amp; Bachmann, A. O. (2000) Ventilatory structures in Cryphocricos barozzii Signoret (Heteroptera, Naucoroidea). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 60 (2), 267 - 273. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0034 - 71082000000200010" type="journal article" year="2000">
Lopez Ruf 
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF9201D6F81952C49899" box="[906,961,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
(2000)
</bibRefCitation>
described the ventilatory structures of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF9202EBF83C503798FD" authorityName=": Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[183,306,1980,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryptocricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF9202EBF83C503798FD" box="[183,306,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and compared them to those of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E076FF9200FFF83C558198FD" authority="(Fabricius, 1794)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[675,1156,1980,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E076FF9200FFF83C52B298FD" box="[675,951,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="74">Aphelocheirus aestivalis</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1794)
</taxonomicName>
. They suggested the two genera are more closely related than previously thought because the specialized plastron system could not have evolved convergently. However, a molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930176FF1752D29F9A" authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[810,983,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cryphocricinae">Cryphocricinae</taxonomicName>
(Reynoso-Velasco &amp; Sites, in prep.) and upcoming phylogeny of the entire family by RWS indicate the opposite, that 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF93064CFF3B55CC9FFE" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1851" box="[1040,1225,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aphelocheiridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930758FF3B54999FFE" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[1284,1436,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930758FF3B54999FFE" box="[1284,1436,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and most likely the Papuan genus 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930047FF5F53839FD2" authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[539,646,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Idiocarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930047FF5F53839FD2" box="[539,646,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Idiocarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) evolved plastron systems convergently. 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF93060DFF5F55B99FD2" authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1897" box="[1105,1212,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Idiocarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF93060DFF5F55B99FD2" box="[1105,1212,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Idiocarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been shown to have plastral respiration, although it lives in fast, highly oxygenated streams and has alary dimorphism with the brachypterous form predominant.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FCA5667DE077FF9302CBFB8C53469BBB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693075" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4693075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693075/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" startId="3.[151,264,1036,1060]" targetBox="[151,1435,342,1010]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="A86536F5E077FF9302CBFB8C53469BBB" blockId="3.[151,1437,1036,1168]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF9302CBFB8C503E9B0F" bold="true" box="[151,315,1036,1060]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">FIGURES 1–4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF93031EFB8C53269B0F" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[322,547,1036,1060]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF93031EFB8C53269B0F" box="[322,547,1036,1060]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Cryphocricos barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(1) holotype, (2) brachypterous female from Rosario River, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, (3) abdominal terga showing dark tubercles near middle of III–V, (4) subgenital plate of two specimens from Nova Teutonia, Brazil showing intrapopulational variation in shape of posterior margin. Figure 1 courtesy of NHMW 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF9306C0FBD4544E9B47" authority="Image" authorityName="Image" box="[1180,1355,1108,1132]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hemiptera Image</taxonomicName>
Collection / Harald Bruckner and Herbert Zettel.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A86536F5E077FF93029BFB3F50019AFF" blockId="3.[151,1437,1214,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">
In a treatment of species of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF9303A3FB3E53929BF3" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[511,663,1214,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF9303A3FB3E53929BF3" box="[511,663,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known or thought to occur in 
<collectingCountry id="D0CD7665E077FF9301B7FB3E55589BF3" box="[1003,1117,1214,1240]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF930635FB3F54349BF3" author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[1129,1329,1214,1241]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="103 - 120" refId="ref13109" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1991) El genero Cryphocricos en la Argentina (Hemiptera-Limnocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 49 (1 - 4), 103 - 120." type="journal article" year="1991">Lopez Ruf (1991)</bibRefCitation>
provided a detailed diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF9303F8FB63531B9BD7" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[420,542,1250,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF9303F8FB63531B9BD7" box="[420,542,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and descriptions of nymphal instars 1–3 and 5 and later revised her description of instar 3 (
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF930345FA8650D39A0A" author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[281,470,1286,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="120 - 121" refId="ref13147" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1996) Nuevas consideraciones sobre Cryphocricos barozzii Signoret y descripcion de la ninfa III (Insecta- Heteroptera-Limnocoridae). Physis, B 51, 120 - 121." type="journal article" year="1996">Lopez Ruf 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Because she could not locate the 
<typeStatus id="77618857E077FF93013DFA8752919A0A" box="[865,916,1287,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">type</typeStatus>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF9301FCFA87556C9A0B" author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[928,1129,1286,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="103 - 120" refId="ref13109" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1991) El genero Cryphocricos en la Argentina (Hemiptera-Limnocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 49 (1 - 4), 103 - 120." type="journal article" year="1991">Lopez Ruf (1991)</bibRefCitation>
based her identification on comparison of the curvature of the lateral margins of her specimens with that in a drawing by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF9306C0FAAA544A9A6E" author="Signoret, V." box="[1180,1359,1322,1349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="289 - 291" refId="ref13706" refString="Signoret, V. (1850) Description d'un genre nouveau de l'ordre des Hemipteres Heteropteres, et de la section des Hydrocoryses. Revue et magasin de zoologie pure et appliquee, 2, 289 - 291." type="journal article" year="1850">Signoret (1850)</bibRefCitation>
. I have not seen a drawing in the original description by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF9300E6FACE52689A42" author="Signoret, V." box="[698,877,1358,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="289 - 291" refId="ref13706" refString="Signoret, V. (1850) Description d'un genre nouveau de l'ordre des Hemipteres Heteropteres, et de la section des Hydrocoryses. Revue et magasin de zoologie pure et appliquee, 2, 289 - 291." type="journal article" year="1850">Signoret (1850)</bibRefCitation>
, but if it exists, his rendering of the lateral margin cannot be considered a reliable diagnostic characteristic by which to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930664FAF355B19AA7" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[1080,1204,1394,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930664FAF355B19AA7" box="[1080,1204,1394,1421]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all congeners; thus, the descriptive information in this paper should be considered suspect unless validated by the examination of vouchers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E0C0657EE077FF9402CBFA5E542E9E86" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A86536F5E077FF9302CBFA5E546199A3" blockId="3.[151,1437,1214,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF9302CBFA5E50119AD3" bold="true" box="[151,276,1502,1528]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The original description (
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF930061FA5E53E59AD2" author="Signoret, V." box="[573,736,1502,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="289 - 291" refId="ref13706" refString="Signoret, V. (1850) Description d'un genre nouveau de l'ordre des Hemipteres Heteropteres, et de la section des Hydrocoryses. Revue et magasin de zoologie pure et appliquee, 2, 289 - 291." type="journal article" year="1850">Signoret 1850</bibRefCitation>
) is translated to English as follows: Generally brown. Below a little lighter. Yellowish head and beak, as well as antennae and legs. Granular head and prothorax, very flat, and lateral margins of the latter crenulate. Elytra flattened, finely granulate, and extending over the body below.Anterior femora granular and browner than the insect; the posterior femora yellowish, as well as the tibia. Length 0, 011; width 1, 006. In a redescription, the size was reported as 
<quantity id="6F229B10E077FF930149F9EE527C99A2" box="[789,889,1646,1673]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.02" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="10.2">10.2 mm</quantity>
length and 
<quantity id="6F229B10E077FF9301A0F9EE553899A2" box="[1020,1085,1646,1673]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
width (
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF9306CEF9EE545D99A3" author="Montandon, A. L." box="[1170,1368,1646,1672]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="6 - 23" refId="ref13311" refString="Montandon, A. L. (1897) Hemiptera Cryptocerata. Fam. Naucoridae. - Sous-fam. Cryptocricinae. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologische-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 47, 6 - 23." type="journal article" year="1897">Montandon 1897</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A86536F5E077FF93029BF913523A9817" blockId="3.[151,1437,1214,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">
In a comparison with macropterous 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930034F91352CA9987" authority=", Montandon (1911)" authorityName=", Montandon" authorityYear="1911" box="[616,975,1682,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breddini">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930034F91353EF9987" box="[616,746,1682,1709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">C. breddini</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CC4B4B04E077FF9300A6F91252CA9987" author="Montandon, A. L." box="[762,975,1682,1708]" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" pagination="83 - 94" refId="ref13346" refString="Montandon, A. L. (1911) Nouvelles especes d'Hydrocorises appartenant aux collections du Museum Entomologique de Berlin. Bulletin de la Societe Roumanie des Sciences, 20 (1), 83 - 94." type="journal article" year="1911">Montandon (1911)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
provided features to distinguish it from brachypterous 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930361F93750B299FB" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[317,439,1718,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930361F93750B299FB" box="[317,439,1718,1745]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, most of these features are related to differences between wing morphs and are not necessarily interspecific differences. At the time, these were the only two species described; thus, because these features are fairly ubiquitous they are of little use to distinguish among the species currently described. He also reported both species to be of nearly identical size and color.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A86536F5E077FF94029BF8C6542E9E86" blockId="3.[151,1437,1214,2033]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">
After examining thousands of specimens of the genus, I have discovered a feature apparently unique to 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E077FF930763F8C751B998AF" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E077FF930763F8C751B998AF" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dark tuberculation of the abdominal terga in brachypterous specimens tends to be sparse and limited to the anterior terga (
<figureCitation id="30E12A70E077FF930360F80E50AC9883" box="[316,425,1934,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1036,1060]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetId="figure-85@3.[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Cryphocricos barozzii (1) holotype, (2) brachypterous female from Rosario River, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, (3) abdominal terga showing dark tubercles near middle of III–V, (4) subgenital plate of two specimens from Nova Teutonia, Brazil showing intrapopulational variation in shape of posterior margin. Figure 1 courtesy of NHMW Hemiptera Image Collection / Harald Bruckner and Herbert Zettel." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693075/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="75">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
). More specifically, the tubercles are only on terga III and IV and sometimes a few appear in the paramedian areas of tergum V (anteriorly on fused tergum V of males). On some specimens, the tubercles appear only on the median halves of terga III and IV, whereas on others the tubercles are distributed further laterally. The abdominal tubercle condition of the 
<typeStatus id="77618857E070FF94003BFF1753CC9F9A" box="[615,713,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">holotype</typeStatus>
was confirmed by Herbert Zettel (pers. comm.). The restriction of the abdominal tubercles anteriorly is distinct and appears to be diagnostic for this species, and is clearly different than the condition of other species in which the abdomen is usually either devoid of, or covered with, tubercles. The female subgenital plate exhibits a moderate amount of variation in the shape of the posterior margin; the rounded posterolateral lobes are sometimes well-developed and an incipient medial lobe also can be present (
<figureCitation id="30E12A70E070FF94075CFEA754439E6A" box="[1280,1350,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1036,1060]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetId="figure-85@3.[151,1435,342,1010]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Cryphocricos barozzii (1) holotype, (2) brachypterous female from Rosario River, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, (3) abdominal terga showing dark tubercles near middle of III–V, (4) subgenital plate of two specimens from Nova Teutonia, Brazil showing intrapopulational variation in shape of posterior margin. Figure 1 courtesy of NHMW Hemiptera Image Collection / Harald Bruckner and Herbert Zettel." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693075/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Many museum collections hold Fritz Plaumann specimens from Nova Teutonia, 
<collectingCountry id="D0CD7665E070FF940187FECB55279E4E" box="[987,1058,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and I have a series from Rosario River in 
<collectingRegion id="6A1EF817E070FF9402ABFEEF50CF9EA2" box="[247,458,367,393]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
; these are all 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E070FF940002FEEF53D29EA2" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[606,727,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E070FF940002FEEF53D29EA2" box="[606,727,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the newly discovered abdominal tubercle feature, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="6FDA4D76E070FF940362FE1350B29E86" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[318,439,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barozzii">
<emphasis id="9AAEEAE7E070FF940362FE1350B29E86" box="[318,439,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">C. barozzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 
<collectingRegion id="6A1EF817E070FF94007FFE1353C29E86" box="[547,711,403,429]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="6A1EF817E070FF9400A1FE1352CB9E86" box="[765,974,403,429]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
in the extreme south of 
<collectingCountry id="D0CD7665E070FF940683FE1354229E86" box="[1247,1319,403,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="76">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
